<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-Wgf2Aw-_DgM/WHpmP3IX5rI/AAAAAAAALeI/vV8ELi4P71MQ3TkQCgXSaNsHEgUzfk5ZACLcB/s1600/AP1140133.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="410" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-Wgf2Aw-_DgM/WHpmP3IX5rI/AAAAAAAALeI/vV8ELi4P71MQ3TkQCgXSaNsHEgUzfk5ZACLcB/s640/AP1140133.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-hJBVm82EY0o/WHpmQ27mw0I/AAAAAAAALeM/JsiIBmt8JBg4cGtEWPlocrik4pJ_rCFTQCLcB/s1600/AP1140136.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="466" src="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-hJBVm82EY0o/WHpmQ27mw0I/AAAAAAAALeM/JsiIBmt8JBg4cGtEWPlocrik4pJ_rCFTQCLcB/s640/AP1140136.jpg" width="640" /></a></div>Another fine day to be on the hills for the start of the Two Day Winter Skills Course with Chris, Glen and Helen. The White Corries chairlift provided an easy ride to the upper slopes of <i>Meall a Bhuiridh</i> where the first task of the day was to look at and practice using ice axe, boots and crampons. It took a bit of searching to find suitable snow for sliding on; what was there being either old snow frozen hard or soft and deep powder. This gave a fast or slow sliding option but nothing really of the desirable middling speed. We made things work however running through the full repertoire of unplanned sliding scenarios. What was good though was the variety of ground that we had to crampon around on. Neve, bare rock, frozen turf, ice; we had it all to play with. In our wandering about we ticked the mountain's Munro summit and made it back to the chairlift just as the lift operators were starting to look impatient.<a href="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-MgUlwzKFl90/WHpnTYuOreI/AAAAAAAALes/YtFOPol_3Y4aUQpbsvCzDhI8-jbL9UlbQCLcB/s1600/AP1140143.jpg" style=